result.formatted_address: G, 83 Catchick St, Kennedy Town, Hong Kong
result.name: Jaspa's

reviews.text: Amazing venue, love the outdoor seating which accommodates dogs and smokers. I've only ever been for breakfast of which they have plenty of options all delicious and some healthier than others and great coffee! All in all Good bang for your buck.

Wings were very crispy, which I love. I didn't appreciate the sweet sauce that accompanied them however. Service was not stellar. Great K- Town ambiance and good" crazy hour" prices on drinks. Our friends had a quesadilla which was a good size with big chunks of grilled chicken. Calamari was okay but the star was the chicken and vegetables. It came with two whole chicken breasts!

Wait staff managed to get half the orders wrong. The snapper was explained as being as big as the steak. When it turned up, it was smaller than the set menu fish which is less than half the price. When I talked to the manager he said he would charge me a set menu price. However his attitude was terrible. Castello restaurants are terribly managed. Will never come back. There’s more care and service at McDonalds.
good food. good price. great service

Good environment,  and the light is soft and makes people feel comfortable.  Food is delicious. Service manner is good, but needs to improve a little bit that is to be proactive such as to add water before customers to request.  We will come again next time.
